Tournament of Souls

Developer

Riot Games Inc.

Publisher(s)

Riot Games Inc.

Release Date(s)

July 20, 2023

Platform(s)

Microsoft Windows

Genre

Fighting Game, Game Mode

Modes

Single-player

Format

Internet

Input methods

Keyboard, Mouse

System Requirements

League of Legends

The Tournament of Souls is a fighting game-style metagame in League of Legends telling the story of Samira's rise to fame in the Tournament of Souls. It was released on July 20th, 2023 (1:00 PM PT) and ended on August 28th, 2023 (11:59 PT).[1][2]

Lore[]

"Frontier's whatever you want it to be."
This story occurs in another universe within the Multiverse, separate from the main Runeterra Prime universe.

Tournament of Souls

By Taylor Dinwiddie, Ty Sheedlo

Play League of Legends to build Samira's reputation and style on your competition at the Tournament of Souls! Face off against the strongest soul fighters in a series of fierce 1v1 matches to help Samira chase down her biggest bounty yet and fulfill her SOUL'S DESIRE!

Starring: Evelynn, Gwen, Jhin, Lux, Naafiri, Pyke, Samira, Sett, Shaco, Viego

Mentioned: Isolde

Samira: Now that's more like it. Try to keep up, softie.

Back into the mix with fight SIX! This stealthy DEMA agent is silent as the night and swift as a snake! Captivating all who stand in her way and goin' in for the kill while their defenses are down, Evelynn is one VICIOUS experiment, folks! Keep the damage tickin', or she'll remain alive and kickin'!

Samira: Pfft, what kind of woman do you take me for?

Evelynn: Everyone's got something that makes them tick, love.

Samira: Wow. Big talk from someone with manufactured powers. Let me show you what natural talent looks like.

Victory

Samira: Only an idiot hunts a hunter.

Defeat
Evelynn: Victory is always so... delicious.

Oh man, OH MAN! Sett's here for fight number SEVEN! He's built like a tank and punches even harder, so just make sure you don't say a THING about his momma! The only way you're takin' this behemoth down is if you can shatter his defenses before he crushes your spine AND your tourney run!

Sett: Famed bounty hunter versus even-more-famed champion brawler? What is this, the showdown of the century?

Samira: Keep telling yourself that. To me, it's just another fight.

Sett: It's okay to show a little emotion, Samira. It won't hurt ya. But... I will.

Samira: You can drop the tough guy act, kid. I'll sign your autograph book after I beat you.

Victory

Samira: You just weren't ready for the big leagues, kid.

Defeat

Here we go! THE GRANDDDDD FINALS! This trickster's fighting style is so mysterious that even I can't predict what he'll do next! All I know is that those daggers don't mess around, even if Shaco does! Pierce through his clones and malicious tricks, and you'll have your SOUL'S DESIRE FULFILLED!

Shaco: OoOoOooO... Samira. Have your eye on the prize, yes? But Viego has his eye on you...

Samira: That creepy monster doesn't scare me. I fight my own battles.

Shaco: Not all puppets have strings, mmMmMmmM. You will do as Eye have seen, even if you do not know it.

Samira: Did you see me kicking your ass? Because I'm about to.

Victory

Samira: Was that it? A bundle of empty clothes with creepy eyes is the best Viego has to offer?!

Defeat
Shaco: HhHhHhhHhh... Eye did not foresee this outcome. No matter. There are others...

Uh... I think our tournament host JUST JUMPED INTO THE ARENA! This broody fighter loves to take what he can't have, including his own soul power! Viego calls it the power of love, but who knows if his wife would agree! He can't let go of the past and is gonna turn all that grief into YOUR problem now!

Viego:I have been watching you from my tower. Your soul is... strong.

Samira: True power, huh? Let's see it.

Victory

Samira: Thanks, Viego. Time for my payday.

Defeat

Are you SEEING what I'm seeing?! It's hard to tell what's goin' on through all the smoke, but our host does NOT pay me enough for... whatever this showdown's shaping up to be! He's sure to pull out all the stops, so be prepared for anything! Let's hear it one last time for SAMIRA, the One-Eyed Blaze!

God's Eye Viego: I carry her with me always. My lost love, Isolde. Now you see my soul's true form!

Samira: You carry her? Seems like she's the one doing the heavy lifting.

God's Eye Viego: No! She is but a broken reflection. Yet... with the Eye's full strength restored...

Samira: You and your precious Eye... tsk. You borrowed your power, Viego. I earned mine.

Victory

Samira: I've faced my demons, Viego. Time you faced yours.

Defeat
God's Eye Viego: Do you feel it, Isolde? The Eye, reinvigorated! It will bring you to me!!!

I'm rooting for Gwen and Pyke to win it all. I mean, I know technically only one can win, but I just really want them BOTH to get their souls' desires. That can happen, right? There's gotta be a way.

Check this out! In this story, Pyke goes on a killing spree, and the only one who can stop him... is Gwen! It's about the hardest strings to cut being the ones tied closest to our hearts!

Okay...Ooor... how about this one! Pyke and Gwen venture into the Forest of Lost Souls and fight a giant spider, and Pyke rips off one of its fangs AND uses it as weapon! Isn't that SO DISGUSTING?!

After beating Gwen

Congrats to you, Samira! Good luck in the rest of the tournament!

Have I told you about my story where Pyke and Gwen get kidnapped by a mad scientist and sewn into a single person?! It's about how even best friends need space sometimes.

After beating Pyke

WOW! You just keep winning, don't you?! That's amazing! Really! I'm SO happy for you! ...That is some serious plot armor if I've ever seen it...

How did you get so strong? What's your story? You know what? I'm not going to let this get me down... I'm going to channel it into a new comic! That's what I'll do!

Pyke's defeated by an opponent with many weapons... Maybe he can hear voices from the Lands Beyond that teach him how to fight against each of them? IT'S HAPPENING! THE IRON'S HOT! WHERE'S MY PEN?!

Don't you think it's cool how Gwen's thread has healing powers? In a way, I hope these stories are kind of like my threads. The right story at the right time can mean a lot, you know?

Well anyways, in this comic, Gwen stitches Pyke back together, but the thread was corrupted with a wicked curse, and it goes horribly wrong, and he has to eat brains to survive!

...That's it! This one's just about Pyke eating brains, and I love it!

After beating God's Eye Viego

Samira!! What's that portal thing?! It reminds me of that movie 'LOUD' where aliens with no eyes came through a portal and started hunting people with their sonar screeching.... really hope that's not what's happening.

Gameplay[]

Samira Abilities[]

Upon entering battle, Samira will have three available abilities - Q, W, and E. Each ability allows Samira to attack with either her guns (Q) or her sword (W, E). Every time she switches weapons (guns into sword or sword into guns), she increases her Style by one rank on the following scale: E > D > C > B > A > S. Hitting "S" enables her to use her Ultimate (R), which inflicts massive damage and resets the Style meter back to E. Samira begins with a basic set of abilities that she can customize as she progresses through the tournament.

Status Effects[]

Many abilities inflict positive or negative status effects, altering the flow of battle. You can hover over a status effect's icon to learn more about it.

  • Airborne - Knocked into the sky and unable to use abilities for a set time.
  • Bleeding - Taking damage over time.
  • Crit Up - Increased critical hit chance.
  • FATAL - Marked for deathwill be executed the next time they are damaged by an Ultimate ability.
  • Resist - Take reduced incoming damage.
  • Siphoned - A portion of health is stolen and can only be recovered by dealing damage. If stolen health is not recovered in time, take damage equal to the amount of stolen health and the debuff ends.
  • Stealthed - Invulnerable to most incoming damage, except damage over time.
  • Stunned - Cannot attack or take any actions.
  • Unstoppable - Abilities cannot be interrupted.
  • Wounded - Healing is reduced.

Reputation[]

Once you've beaten an opponent, you'll only be able to progress to the next one by earning enough Reputation. You can increase your reputation by completing missions in the Soul Fighter Event.

  • Gain 1 Reputation for every 200 points gathered for the infinite pass mission.
  • Gain 5 Reputation for each 2023 Soul Fighter mission completed.
  • Gain 3 or 4 Reptutation from Arena missions.

Trivia[]

  • Soul Juice Raptor is a reference to Milkshake Duck.[3]
  • God's Eye Viego was created by applying an in-game filter over Soul Fighter Viego's sprite suite, as such he has no hand drawn sprite.[4] A special sprite was created for the purposes of documentation.
